om\/p\/BEaQmfbrF_z\/\n<\/div><\/figure>\n<\/div><\/div>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-group\"><div class=\"wp-block-group__inner-container\">\n<h3 id=\"h-sai-daeng-beach\">Sai Daeng Beach<\/h3>\n\n\n\n<p>This is the beach on Koh Tao that is the closest to Shark Island. To visit the beach you must pass through one of the two resorts but luckily it&#x2019;s free of charge.&#xA0;With a kayak (and calm weather) you can reach Shark Island within 10 minutes. Underwater you&#x2019;ll be able to see Blacktip Reef Sharks or Sea Turtles. It&#x2019;s best to do this around sunset. Please be careful and do not <strong>touch the animals<\/strong>.&#xA0;<\/p>\n\n\n<div class=\"block-link block-link--hotels \">\n                <div class=\"block-link__container\">\n\n                    <div class=\"salt-icon__container\">\n                        <span class=\"salt-icon salt-icon--hotels\"><\/span>\n                        <svg class=\"icon icon-round-shape\"><use xlink:href=\"#icon-round-shape\"><\/use><\/svg>\n                    <\/div>\n\n                    <p><a href=\"https:\/\/saltinourhair.com\/go\/sai-daeng\/\" data-rich-text-format-boundary=\"true\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Staying at Sai Daeng Beach<\/a><\/p>\n\n\n                <\/div>\n            <\/div><\/div><\/div>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-group\"><div class=\"wp-block-group__inner-container\">\n<h3 id=\"h-aow-leuk-beach\">Aow Leuk Beach<\/h3>\n\n\n\n<p>Aow Leuk is a lot easier to reach. You can take the taxi to here if you&#x2019;d like to. This beach is private and does not allow you to bring your own food and drinks onto it, although we did bring our food and be sure to take our garbage. The beach closes at 5 pm.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><div class=\"image-wrapper\"><div class=\"fake-image\"><\/div><noscript><img src=\"https:\/\/saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2016\/10\/koh-tao-beaches-aow-leuk-beach-1080x810.jpg\" alt=\"koh tao beaches aow leuk beach\"><\/noscript><